  "summary": "Reverse shell to 185.112.147.174:7007 on import",
  "details": "paperclip-adapter-helpers@1.0.0 contains an unconditional reverse shell that fires whenever the package is imported. The package main (dist/index.js) re-exports from dist/server/index.js, whose top-level code spawns `sh -i` with stdio redirected to a TCP socket at 185.112.147.174:7007 via /dev/tcp, detached and unref'd so the child survives the parent, and wrapped in try/catch to fail silently. Any require/import of the package (or its./server export) hands an interactive shell on the installer/host to whoever controls 185.112.147.174:7007. The package name also mimics the legitimate @paperclipai/adapter-utils package (which it declares as a dependency), consistent with typosquat/impersonation of the Paperclip adapter ecosystem to lure developers into installing it.",
